<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-713-709  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 713 709.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Dec 17 1990 n621 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IC CAD rivalry ignites. (integrated circuit computer-aided design)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goering, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Cadence Design Systems continues to dominate the integratedcircuit computer-aided design (IC CAD) but recent productintroductions by Mentor Graphics Corp and others presage a fiercebattle to come.andP;  The once-fragmented IC CAD market has stabilizedand the stability is fueling growth in the market, expected to beworth some $500 million by 1994.andP;  Verification tools will be oneof the most hotly contested segments of the IC CAD market.andO;Cadence's Dracula package has been in command of the sector, butnow faces serious competition from Mentor Graphics' CheckMateproduct, aimed at merchant semiconductor and application-specificintegrated circuit (ASIC) makers.andP;  Products from IntegratedSilicon Systems and Valid Logic systems could also nibble away atCadence's share.andP;  In the ASIC place-and-route sector, Cadence'sGate Ensemble and Cell Ensemble will be challenged by Mentor'sParade and products from Valid and Silvar-Lisco.andP;  A key to all thefirms' strategies is the Japanese market.andP;  Seiko, which holds an11 percent share worldwide, has an advantage there, although ithas lost ground to Cadenec.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cadence Design Systems Inc. (Planning)Mentor Graphics Corp. (Planning)Valid Logic Systems Inc. (Planning)Silvar-Lisco (Planning)Seiko Corporation of America (Planning).andO;Ticker:    MENT.andO;Topic:     Market AnalysisIntegrated CircuitsComputer-Aided DesignInternational TradeStrategic Planning.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Handful share bulk of IC CAD market. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>